Munster GAA have released details of the upcoming senior hurling championship round robin. It will commence on Easter Sunday, April 17th, with All-Ireland champions Limerick travelling to Cork and Waterford hosting Tipperary. As previously announced, Cork have conceded home advantage against Clare because of the impact on Páirc Uí Chaoimh of a concert and the match will take place in Thurles on May 1st. Details of the final matches in the round robin have yet to be announced but they take place on May 22nd at the same time, which has yet to be announced. This year’s Munster hurling final will be played on June 5th at a venue and time to be confirmed when the finalists are known. April 17th: Waterford v Tipperary, Walsh Park, 2.0, Cork v Limerick, Páirc Uí Chaoimh, 4.0pm April 23rd: Limerick v Waterford, TUS Gaelic Grounds, 7.0pm April 24th: Tipperary v Clare, FBD Semple Stadium, 2.0pm May 1st: Cork v Clare, FBD Semple Stadium, 2.0pm May 8th: Limerick v Tipperary, TUS Gaelic Grounds, 2.0pm May 15th: Waterford v Cork, Walsh Park, 2.0; Clare v Limerick, Cusack Park, 4.0pm May 22nd: Tipperary v Cork, FBD Semple Stadium; Clare v Waterford, Cusack Park, time to be confirmed. June 5th: Munster final, details tbc.